  "body": "We should increase the coverage of the newly created clojure integration tests.\r\n\r\nTwo of the most common use cases are to add and delete contacts. \r\n\r\nThe test steps that should be covered in the tests should be:\r\n\r\n1. Create a new account (already covered by steps) & login (we can start from these steps https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/9f9b896eb7fcfac60d55b33a3744480b13d2ba8d/src/status_im/integration_test.cljs#L46 )\r\n2. Simulate adding any user to contacts (check that the contact is added)\r\n3. Remove the contact (make sure that the contact is removed)\r\n\r\nWe want to achieve the closest coverage to what the UI is actually doing.\r\n\r\nTo simulate adding in the UI:\r\n\r\n1. Create a new account\r\n2. Go to Profile\r\n3. Open `Contacts`\r\n4. Click on `Add new contact`\r\n5. Paste a chat key\r\n6. Click on the `Plus` button\r\n7. See the user in contacts\r\n\r\nAnother way:\r\n1. Create a new account\r\n2. Start a new 1-1 chat with any contact\r\n3. Open user's profile from the chat\r\n4. Click on `Add to contacts`\r\n5. See the user in contacts\r\n\r\nTo simulate removing in the UI:\r\n1. Open the contact's profile\r\n2. Click on `Remove from contacts`\r\n3. Make sure that the user is not in contacts anymore",
